title: Boomerang X - weird bug
description:
this happened to me a LOT while playing this game for a little while until I trained myself out of jumping into the Boomerang. until I did it again just now

basically, it seems that if you jump into the Boomerang there's a change you can stuck on the level geometry at the base of the platform and be unable to move

not really a game break or anything since it happens right at the beginning of the game, just mildly annoying when it happens

title: Boomerang X - just a bug I wanted to record
description:
if you go from the Grave of the Yoran Legion to Deepest Folly, sometimes you can go too quickly and the game will not load the next area in time.  

this apparently happens specifically when you're playing a save file in which you already have Oblivion Comet - the place where I drop here is where the fall into the Tuning Court to collect the final ability is. the first time this happened to me it killed my playthrough, however, this time I actually managed to stay calm. If you let yourself fall for a bit and then try to slingshot forward into the level you can get back into it. if you try to do it from above (as I did the first time this happened to me) you'll become stuck in the level's ceiling geometry, and even Oblivion Comet can't get you out. I tried.
